{"id": "EUVD-2023-60498", "enisaUuid": "605ba958-b402-3718-a100-e1e6c6f0906e", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: tls: avoid hanging tasks on the tx_lock\n\nsyzbot sent a hung task report and Eric explains that adversarial\nreceiver may keep RWIN at 0 for a long time, so we are not guaranteed\nto make forward progress. Thread which took tx_lock and went to sleep\nmay not release tx_lock for hours. Use interruptible sleep where\npossible and reschedule the work if it can't take the lock.\n\nTesting: existing selftest passes", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:35", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bde541a57b4204d0a800afbbd3d1c06c9cdb133f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7123a4337bf73132bbfb5437e4dc83ba864a9a1e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/be5d5d0637fd88c18ee76024bdb22649a1de00d6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1f800f6aae57d2d8f63d32fff383017cbc11cf65", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ccf1ccdc5926907befbe880b562b2a4b5f44c087", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f3221361dc85d4de22586ce8441ec2c67b454f5d", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-54306"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-54306"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0bd58458-ca68-3daa-829f-fcd8463e1a9f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.5"}, {"id": "13b726ae-d680-3c1c-a8e0-0f6ff44bbefe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "79ffe6087e9145d2377385cac48d0d6a6b4225a5 <bde541a57b4204d0a800afbbd3d1c06c9cdb133f"}, {"id": "15edbd70-34bd-3610-b653-fae11eebb509", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "79ffe6087e9145d2377385cac48d0d6a6b4225a5 <1f800f6aae57d2d8f63d32fff383017cbc11cf65"}, {"id": "16d04029-95e0-3929-9c37-01c1fd5e532e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.100"}, {"id": "2c46ab56-4722-3218-bbe4-1e7aea21acda", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.18"},